Sentencas: In order to improve the performance of the anode of solid oxide fuel cells, the cermet anodes were synthesized by employing a carbonate co-precipitation method and calcined at different temperatures (500 degrees C-800 degrees C).
Titulo: The effect of calcination temperature on the properties of Ni-SDC cermet anode

Sentencas: The fabrication of pellet from calcined powder was done by uniaxial pressing.
Titulo: The effect of calcination temperature on the properties of Ni-SDC cermet anode

Sentencas: These pellets were then characterized to investigate the effect of calcination temperature on their microstructure, thermal behavior, porosity, and carbonate bonding along with conductivity.
Titulo: The effect of calcination temperature on the properties of Ni-SDC cermet anode

Sentencas: The carbonates formed within the synthesis process has shown a strong effect over the properties of the Ni-SDC.
Titulo: The effect of calcination temperature on the properties of Ni-SDC cermet anode

Sentencas: It is observed that Ni-SDC maintained its chemical compatibility during each process.
Titulo: The effect of calcination temperature on the properties of Ni-SDC cermet anode

Sentencas: The thermal gravimetric analysis showed that more weight loss occurred for the specimen calcined at low temperature.
Titulo: The effect of calcination temperature on the properties of Ni-SDC cermet anode

Sentencas: Due to the porosity increases with calcination electronic conductivity and performance will also be enhanced.
Titulo: The effect of calcination temperature on the properties of Ni-SDC cermet anode
